Cinema-Tver

This project is a cinema aggregator for Tver, designed to collect and serve movie-related data. The project consists of two main components:

Server: Handles API requests, database interactions, and business logic.

Parser: Scrapes and processes movie data from various sources.

🚀 Tech Stack

Backend: Go, GORM, GraphQL

Database: PostgreSQL

Infrastructure: Docker, Docker Compose

📂 Project Structure

.
├── server/         # Backend application
├── parser/         # Data scraping and processing
├── .env            # Environment variables
├── docker-compose.yml # Docker configuration
└── Makefile        # Project automation commands

🛠️ Setup & Installation

1️⃣ Prerequisites

Ensure you have the following installed:

Docker

Docker Compose

2️⃣ Clone the Repository

git clone https://github.com/your-repo/cinema-tver.git
cd cinema-tver

3️⃣ Configure Environment Variables

Create a .env file in the root/server directory and set the required values.

4️⃣ Start the Services

To start the project, run:

make run-server

This will:

Start the backend server

Start the PostgreSQL database

